Path: godot/tutorials/2d/2d_parallax.rst
Summary: This section explains how to achieve infinite repeating textures using Parallax2D and its repeat_size property, and addresses common setup issues.

Parallax2D provides a bonus effect that gives textures the illusion of repeating infinitely. The repeat_size property tells the node to snap its position forward or back when the camera scrolls by the set value. This effect is achieved by adding a single repeat to all the child canvas items offset by the value. While the camera scrolls between the image and its repeat, it invisibly snaps back giving the appearance of a looping image.

Being a delicate effect, it's easy for unfamiliar users to make mistakes with their setup. Let's go over the "how" and "why" of a few common problems users encounter.
---CHUNK---
