Summary: Explains how to handle image sizing issues for parallax backgrounds in Godot.
The infinite repeat effect is easiest to work with when you have an image designed to repeat seamlessly and is the same size or larger than your viewport before setting the repeat_size property. If you aren't able to obtain assets that are designed for this task, there are some other things you can do to better prepare your image in regards to size.

Here is an example of a texture that is too small for its viewport:

We can see that the viewport size is 500x300 but the texture is 288x208. If we set the repeat_size to the size of our image, the infinite repeat effect doesn't scroll properly because the original texture doesn't cover the viewport. If we set the repeat_size to the size of the viewport, we have a large gap. What can we do?
---CHUNK---
