Summary: This section explains how to scale Parallax2D layers to adjust their size.
To scale the Parallax2D layers, you can adjust the scale property of the Parallax2D node itself. This will scale all child textures proportionally. This method is suitable if you do not require a pixel-perfect look and can tolerate some blurriness.
Key Rule: Adjust the scale property of the Parallax2D node to scale all child textures.
---CHUNK---
